
What is  Git?
It is mainly used for source code management in s/w development but it is able to be used to keep track of modifications in any set of documents or files

 How can you create a repository in Git?
This is probably the most frequently asked question and the answer to this is really simple.
To create a repository, create a directory for the project if it does not exist, then run the command “git init”. By running this command .git directory will be created in the project directory.

what are the main commands in git?
 1)git clone URL
 2)git branch branchname-its used for create branch
 3)git checkout branchname-its used for switced to another branch
 4)git branch -d branchname -its used for delete branch
 5)git branch -a   its used for list the branches
 
 how to commit the code?
    git add filename
    git commit -m "message"
    git push -u origin branchname
 
